Question: How would you invite your friends to a party if phones and the Internet did not exist?
Answer:
If phones and the Internet would not exist I think I would just show up to my friends' place to invite them to a party or even start a party here. This strategy is actually quite good because your friend will feel less confortable refusing to go out directly in front of you. If the party is really important however I might send them a letter or a card of invitation.